<div class="articleBody">
        
    
                                                                                <p>
                    R. Richard Rubottom, a diplomat who influenced and helped hone United States policy toward Latin America in the late 1950s, a time of economic and political tumult that culminated in <a href="http://topics.nytimes.com/top/reference/timestopics/people/c/fidel_castro/index.html?inline=nyt-per" title="More articles about Fidel Castro." class="meta-per">Fidel Castro</a>&rsquo;s takeover in Cuba, died Dec. 6 in Austin, Tex. He was 98.        </p>
                                                </div>
<div class="articleInline runaroundLeft">
    						<div class="inlineImage module">
	<div class="image">
		         <div class="icon enlargeThis"><a href="javascript:pop_me_up2('http://www.nytimes.com/imagepages/2010/12/20/rubottom-obit.html','rubottom_obit_html','width=720,height=642,scrollbars=yes,toolbars=no,resizable=yes')">Enlarge This Image</a></div>
